{
  "texts": [
    "Architecture ReviewThe architecture comprises several key components.",
    "The shard allocator determines partitioning strategies based on the capabilities of each device.",
    "Edge device nodes are responsible for executing individual segments of the large language model (LLM) and logging intermediate outputs.",
    "An aggregator component collects these logs, coordinates feedback mechanisms, and distributes updates to the reward model across the network.",
    "Key FeaturesThe system provides audit trails through tamper-evident logs maintained at each device, ensuring robust traceability."
  ]
}